ved\nassuming a solar-like double-term law with a lap time of $\\approx$ 400 d. Our\norbital solutions result in a period of 10.387678 $\\pm$ 0.000003 days for the\nclose orbit and 2726 $\\pm$ 7 d ($\\approx$ 7.5 yr) for the wide orbit. A\nLomb-Scarge (L-S) periodogram of the pre-whitened $V$-band data reveals a\nstrong single peak providing a rotation period of 10.391 $\\pm$ 0.008 d.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 17 Jun 2016 12:23:43 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 23 Jun 2016 15:33:54 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-08-10"}
